# Adverant Nexus Open Core - Dual License

This project is licensed under a dual-license model:

## Apache License 2.0 (Open Source Core)

The **core functionality** of Adverant Nexus is licensed under the Apache License 2.0.
This includes:

- GraphRAG core storage and retrieval (episodic memory, vector search, graph storage)
- MageAgent core orchestration (multi-agent coordination, task management, streaming)
- Basic API Gateway functionality
- Core authentication (JWT, OAuth basics)
- Shared TypeScript packages and utilities
- CLI tools (`@adverant/nexus-cli`)
- Docker and Kubernetes deployment manifests
- Community plugins (publicly available on GitHub)

See [LICENSE-APACHE-2.0](./LICENSE-APACHE-2.0) for full terms.

**You are free to**:
- Use commercially
- Modify and distribute
- Use privately
- Patent use
- Sublicense

## Elastic License 2.0 (Enterprise Features)

**Enterprise-only features** are licensed under the Elastic License 2.0.
This includes:

### GraphRAG Enterprise
- GDPR compliance tools (Right to Delete, Right to Access, Data Portability)
- Multi-tenant row-level security (RLS)
- Advanced query optimization
- Google Drive/Notion/Confluence ingestion
- Real-time document change detection

### MageAgent Enterprise
- Smart Model Router (cost optimization across providers)
- Agent Pre-Warmer (cold-start elimination)
- Performance Profiler & Analytics Dashboard
- Autonomous mode (self-directed task execution)
- Cross-team collaboration features

### Enterprise Infrastructure
- Advanced monitoring and observability
- Auto-scaling and load balancing
- Enterprise SSO (SAML, LDAP, Okta, Auth0)
- Audit logging and compliance reporting
- SLA guarantees and priority support

See [LICENSE-ELASTIC](./LICENSE-ELASTIC) for full terms.

**Elastic License restrictions**:
- ❌ You may NOT provide this software as a hosted or managed SaaS service
- ❌ You may NOT circumvent license key functionality
- ✅ You CAN use it internally within your organization
- ✅ You CAN modify and distribute (subject to restrictions)

## How to determine which license applies

Check the `.visibility.json` file at the root of this repository for a comprehensive
mapping of which files/directories fall under which license.

**General rule**:
- If in doubt, assume Apache 2.0 for core packages
- Enterprise features are clearly marked in source code comments
- Proprietary enterprise code is NOT included in this repository

